    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-pollock-curry-with-green-beans/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> roughly (chop them in one bunch for speed!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-pollock-curry-with-green-beans/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong> with 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>- this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-pollock-curry-with-green-beans/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric, chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger paste</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-pollock-curry-with-green-beans/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chopped green beans</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-pollock-curry-with-green-beans/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Sit your <strong>diced pollock </strong>over the sauce and cook, covered, for 4-5 min or until cooked through (unevenly sized diced pollock? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!)</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Once done, gently stir everything together (add a splash more water if your curry is looking a little thick!) \u2013 this is your <strong>coconut pollock curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-pollock-curry-with-green-beans/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Squeeze your pouch[es] of <strong>cooked brown long grain rice </strong>to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] (just a little!) and put the pouch in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two or more pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-pollock-curry-with-green-beans/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>coconut pollock curry</strong> with the <strong>cooked rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with your <strong>black sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
